f(x,y)
\dfrac{xf'_{x}}{f'_{y}}+\dfrac{yf'_{y}}{f'_{x}}+x+y=C
f(x,y)
C
f(x,y)
f(x,y)=0
f''(x)=0
f''(x)\neq 0
y=f(x)
Y-f(x)=f'(x)[X-x]
X=-\dfrac{f(x)}{f'(x)}+x,Y=f(x)-xf'(x)
f(x)-xf'(x)+x-\dfrac{f(x)}{f'(x)}=C
f'(x)-f'(x)-x[f'(x)]^2+1-\dfrac{[f'(x)]^2-f(x)f''(x)}{(f'(x))^2}=0
\Longrightarrow xf''(x)=\dfrac{f(x)f''(x)}{[f'(x)]^2}
f(x)=kx+b
[f'(x)]=\dfrac{f(x)}{x}\Longrightarrow \sqrt{f(x)}+\sqrt{x}=C
\sqrt{y}+\sqrt{x}=C
